    "title" : "EduAdmin Pro API",
    "description" : "The EduAdmin Pro REST API provides programmatic access to school management operations\nincluding student records, staff management, fees, grades, timetables, and administration.\n\n## Base URL\n```\nhttps://api.eduadminpro.com/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\nAll endpoints (except `/auth/login` and `/auth/register`) require a valid JWT Bearer token\nin the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <your_token>\n```\n\nTokens expire after **24 hours**. Use `/auth/refresh` to obtain a new token without\nre-entering credentials.\n\n## Role-Based Access\nEduAdmin Pro uses five roles with different permission levels:\n| Role | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `super_admin` | Full system access |\n| `admin` | School-level administration |\n| `teacher` | Class and grade management |\n| `student` | Read-only access to own records |\n| `parent` | Read-only access to linked student records |\n\n## Response Format\nAll responses return JSON with the following envelope:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {},\n  \"message\": \"Operation successful\",\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"page\": 1,\n    \"per_page\": 20,\n    \"total\": 100\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Rate Limiting\nRequests are limited to **300 per minute** per API token. Rate limit headers are included\nin every response:\n- `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Maximum requests per minute\n- `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Requests remaining in current window\n- `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Unix timestamp when the window resets\n",
